abstract: A burn-it-down candidate is topping a splintered field of more moderate contenders and setting the party’s establishment wing on edge.

abstract: Democratic presidential candidate Elizabeth Warren rallied a rowdy crowd in Seattle Saturday night as ballots for Washington state's March 10 presidential primary began arriving in mailboxes of the state’s nearly 4.5 million voters.
snippet: Democratic presidential candidate Elizabeth Warren rallied a rowdy crowd in Seattle Saturday night as ballots for Washington state's March 10 presidential primary began arriving in mailboxes of the state’s nearly 4.5 million voters.
lead_paragraph: SEATTLE — Democratic presidential candidate Elizabeth Warren rallied a rowdy crowd in Seattle Saturday night as ballots for Washington state's March 10 presidential primary began arriving in mailboxes of the state’s nearly 4.5 million voters.
headline_main: Warren Rallies Packed Seattle Crowd, Slams Bloomberg
headline_print_headline: Warren Rallies Packed Seattle Crowd, Slams Bloomberg

abstract: The Vermont senator defeated his opponents by a large margin, showing strength with minority and working-class voters. But the other candidates vowed to fight on.

abstract: There’s the democracy-in-action proselytizer, the resigned skeptic and the thoroughly bewildered. All made their way to Coronado High School in Nevada to help pick a presidential nominee.
snippet: There’s the democracy-in-action proselytizer, the resigned skeptic and the thoroughly bewildered. All made their way to Coronado High School in Nevada to help pick a presidential nominee.
lead_paragraph: HENDERSON, Nev. — One voter was under the mistaken impression that he had come to a primary, not a caucus. Another had planned to vote for former New York mayor Michael R. Bloomberg, only to discover he was not on the ballot. And a third had a multipart procedural question for the volunteer running his precinct caucus at Coronado High School.

abstract: Nevada caucus officials and voters at multiple sites on Saturday reported voting rules confusion, calculation glitches and delays in reporting tallies - despite efforts to avoid the issues that plagued Iowa's caucuses earlier this month.

lead_paragraph: LAS VEGAS — Senator Bernie Sanders claimed a major victory in the Nevada caucuses on Saturday that demonstrated his broad appeal in the first racially diverse state in the presidential primary race and established him as the clear front-runner for the Democratic nomination.

abstract: U.S. Senator Bernie Sanders, often maligned by opponents as a liberal outsider who cannot unify the Democratic Party, won the party's Nevada caucuses by a comfortable margin thanks to a diverse coalition of supporters, according to polling agency Edison Research.

lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — U.S. Senator Bernie Sanders, often maligned by opponents as a liberal outsider who cannot unify the Democratic Party, won the party's Nevada caucuses by a comfortable margin thanks to a diverse coalition of supporters, according to polling agency Edison Research.
